## 4. Validation Strategy

### 4.1 Validation Chain Details

| Field | Endpoint | Rules | Sanitization |
|-------|----------|-------|--------------|
| `title` | POST, PUT | Required (POST), 1-200 chars | trim(), escape() |
| `description` | POST, PUT | Optional, max 2000 chars, nullable | trim(), escape() |
| `status` | POST, PUT, GET | Optional, enum validation | none |
| `id` | GET, PUT, DELETE | UUID v4 format | trim() |
| `limit` | GET | Optional, 1-100, default 20 | toInt() |
| `offset` | GET | Optional, >= 0, default 0 | toInt() |
| `sortBy` | GET | Optional, createdAt or updatedAt | none |
| `order` | GET | Optional, asc or desc | none |

### 4.2 Custom Validators

**UUID Validator**:
```typescript
const UUID_REGEX = /^[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-4[0-9a-f]{3}-[89ab][0-9a-f]{3}-[0-9a-f]{12}$/i;

.custom((value) => {
  if (!UUID_REGEX.test(value)) {
    throw new Error('Invalid task ID format');
  }
  return true;
})
```

**Nullable String Validator** (for description update):
```typescript
.custom((value) => {
  if (value === null) return true;
  if (typeof value !== 'string') {
    throw new Error('Description must be a string or null');
  }
  return true;
})
```

